      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Raising the minimum wage in low-cost living areas can indeed hurt small businesses more than it helps workers. The increased labor costs can force small shops to raise prices, cut hours, or even close down. While workers might see a temporary boost in income, the overall negative impact on local businesses can lead to job losses and reduced economic activity. The \"increased spending\" theory often doesn't hold up in reality for small businesses, as they can't easily pass on costs to consumers without risking their survival.",
      "source": "target",
